8. Calls for Sudan and South Sudan to resolve Abyei's final status peacefully and consider AU proposals;

9. Urges parties to provide humanitarian personnel with safe access to civilians;

10. Requests the Secretary-General to ensure human rights monitoring and report to the Council;

11. Requests measures to ensure UNISFA's compliance with the UN's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation;

12. Stresses improved cooperation between Sudan and South Sudan is critical for peace and stability;

13. Requests the Secretary-General to report on UNISFA's progress every 60 days and inform the Council of any serious violations;

14. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
